From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 06:50:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: force include cstdint for C++ sources

The pinned EKA2L1 snapshot has several headers that expose std::uint*_t
without including cstdint directly. GCC 13 exposes these transitive
include assumptions in different targets as the build progresses.

Force-include cstdint for C++ translation units so this package can build
reliably without carrying a large header-by-header compatibility patch.

Signed-off-by: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 75103a19..c7d8b9b5 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -5,6 +5,9 @@ project (EKA2L1)
 # Clang 14 is required to compile nicely with C++ 20
 set (CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 17)
 
+# Work around missing direct cstdint includes in the pinned source tree.
+add_compile_options($<$<COMPILE_LANGUAGE:CXX>:-include> $<$<COMPILE_LANGUAGE:CXX>:cstdint>)
+
 option(EKA2L1_BUILD_TOOLS "Build EKA2L1's tool" ON)
 option(EKA2L1_BUILD_TESTS "Build EKA2L1's tests" ON)
 option(EKA2L1_ENABLE_SCRIPTING_ABILITY "Enable to script with Python or Lua" ON)
